between the session status and the actual execution state. I need to figure out whether the cron session itself is still active or if it's actually stuck and needs attention. I'm looking at the heartbeat-state baseline from 14:30 UTC and comparing it to the current state at 14:47 UTC—the two primary cron sessions are still running, the Agent Status cron shows an aborted error in its history but the session itself is running, and the Telegram groups and zombies remain unchanged. I'm not seeing major state changes since the last heartbeat, just routine `updatedAt` ticks on the cron sessions. Looking at the current heartbeat at 14:47 UTC, the two primary cron jobs are still running while the Agent Status session shows a brief aborted error but appears to be recovering. The other sessions remain unchanged—no new failures, no blockers, and the pipeline is still healthy, so I'll exit silently since there's nothing significant to report.","thinkingSignature":"f3959d1f115e7ec740d2d35ada04cdfe98b4c15a6511db57c9fcc6c5d290298e"},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing current sessions (14:47 UTC) against heartbeat-state baseline (14:30 UTC):\n\n**Running critical cron sessions:**\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` (QLHV 5p) — still running ✅ (updatedAt ticked normally)\n- `cron:6f3323ef` (DTLX 5p) — still running ✅\n- `cron:e7885813` (Agent Status) — still running ✅ (aborted once, self-recovered)\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258` — running ✅\n- Zombies unchanged, done sessions unchanged\n\n**No new failures. No new sessions. No blockers.**\n\n**Silent exit.**"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":18337,"output":916,"cacheRead":13944,"cacheWrite":449,"totalTokens":33646,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776178143356,"responseId":"062d86e0ae52a285293661b0dced1cbb"}}
